-- French Open Tennis Final Delayed to Tomorrow Because of Rain
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2012-06-10T18:06:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-10/french-open-tennis-final-delayed-to-tomorrow-because-of-rain.html
The French Open tennis final has
been postponed until tomorrow because of rain, organizers said.  Defending champion  Rafael Nadal  of Spain leads top-ranked
Novak Djokovic of Serbia by two sets to one, and 2-1 down in the
fourth set. Play will be resumed at 1p.m. local time on Monday,
taking the tournament into the third week for the first time
since 1973.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Danielle Rossingh at 
 drossingh@bloomberg.net  